## 🇬🇧 English

### 1. Controller

This app is provided as a private, non-commercial project.  
Contact: chargtrack@outlook.com

---

### 2. Principle: Local Data Storage

ChargTrack processes only data that you enter yourself. **All data is stored locally on your device.** There is no transmission to external servers, no cloud synchronization, and no tracking.

---

### 3. What data is stored?

The app stores only the data you manually enter:

- **Vehicle data:** Name, manufacturer, model, license plate, battery capacity, range, photo
- **Charging sessions:** Date, time, location, energy charged, cost, state of charge, odometer reading, notes
- **Settings:** Currency, consumption unit, language preference

---

### 4. Backup Feature

The backup feature exports your data as a JSON file **exclusively to your device**. This file only leaves your device if you actively share it via iOS's share function. You are responsible for the content of any files you share.

---

### 5. No Third-Party Sharing

Your data is not shared, sold, or otherwise transmitted to third parties.

---

### 6. No Analytics or Tracking Tools

The app does not use analytics services (e.g. Firebase, Crashlytics), advertising networks, or tracking of any kind.

---

### 7. Permissions

The app requires the following device permission:

- **Photo Library (optional):** Only if you add a vehicle photo. Permission is requested only when needed.

---

### 8. Children

This app is not directed at children under the age of 13. No personal data from children is collected.

---

### 9. Changes to This Privacy Policy

Any changes will be published on this page. The date of the last update is shown at the top.

---

### 10. Contact

For questions regarding data protection, please contact: chargtrack@outlook.com
